  "prompt": "How do I filter out US election news in my Quora feed?",
  "response": "To filter out US election news (or any specific topic) from your Quora feed, you can take the following steps:\n\n1. **Mute Topics or Keywords**:\n   - Go to your Quora feed.\n   - Click on the three dots (`...`) next to a post or question related to US elections.\n   - Select **\u201cMute [Topic Name]\u201d** (e.g., \"Mute US Elections\") to stop seeing content related to that topic.\n   - Alternatively, you can go to **Settings > Muted Topics** and manually add specific topics like \"US Elections\" that you want to mute.\n\n2. **Adjust Content Preferences**:\n   - Go to **Settings > Content Preferences**.\n   - Here, you can customize your feed by reducing the visibility of certain topics or keywords.\n\n3. **Use the \u201cNot Interested\u201d Option**:\n   - When you see a post about US elections, click the three dots (`...`) and select **\u201cNot Interested.\u201d**\n   - This tells Quora\u2019s algorithm to show you fewer similar posts.\n\n4. **Block Specific Users**:\n   If you notice certain users frequently posting about US elections, you can block them to stop seeing their content.\n\n5. **Report Irrelevant Content**:\n   If the content is not relevant to you, you can report it by clicking the three dots (`...`) and selecting **\u201cReport.\u201d**\n\n6. **Use Quora Digest Customization**:\n   If you receive Quora Digest emails, you can customize the topics in your email settings to exclude US elections.\n\nBy using these steps, you should be able to reduce or eliminate US election-related content from your Quora feed. However, note that Quora\u2019s algorithm may still occasionally show related content based on your broader interests.",
